82%2F7%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=
=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) color.) Alo, which
dressed ( https://youtu.be/i2TNH61_vs0?feature=3Dshared&utm_campaign=3DLine=
+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBER=
S+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_t=
erm=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) Bengals quarterback Joe Burrow for last night=E2=
=80=99s NFL Honors awards in New Orleans, has also been styling their piece=
s for more wear out of the gym. Alas, I=E2=80=99m not really feeling the bl=
azers with the tacky logo on the upper arm, but they probably think they ne=
ed to signal the expansion. (Remember, the company was in fundraising mode =
not so long ago,
seeking a $10 billion valuation ( https://puck.news/tory-birkenstock-skims-=
and-the-great-fashion-ipo-debate/?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%=
282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm=
_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd1=
2a ). I wonder whatever happened with that=E2=80=A6) That said, the half-zi=
p track jacket ( https://go.shopmy.us/p-12897214?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+=
-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%=
2F7%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df=
6c60617da42abd12a ) feels like the right fit.=C2=A0

Designer
Normcore
--------

At first, I was surprised to see that
R=C3=B9adh ( https://go.shopmy.us/p-12890439?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SU=
BSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%=
2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60=
617da42abd12a ), the newest upscale cool-girl denim line from former AYR an=
d Calvin Klein jeans designer Jac Cameron, had launched at Moda Operandi. F=
or one thing: Why did they choose to partner with M.O., which doesn=E2=80=
=99t have retail stores? (Denim is a try-on category if there ever was one.=
) When I reached out to Cameron, she explained that M.O. gave R=C3=B9adh th=
e opportunity to presell products and
get early feedback=E2=80=94which they=E2=80=99ll use to help understand pro=
duct demand and get a better sense of sizing for their inventory. Also, it =
doesn=E2=80=99t hurt to partner with a company that caters to an elevated, =
selective, and in-the-know customer. (They did a fun party at the top of Ne=
w York Fashion Week that attracted the target audience, from W magazine=E2=
=80=99s Sara Moonves to Magasin=E2=80=99s Laura Reilly.)

=C2=A0

Anyway, R=C3=B9adh also just launched a range of cotton sweatshirts, which =
aligns with another trend: designer normcore ( https://www.nytimes.com/2025=
/01/23/style/normcore-auralee-lemaire-paris.html?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+=
-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%=
2F7%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df=
6c60617da42abd12a ). The newest-ish player in this game is Cotton On ( http=
s://go.shopmy.us/p-12891152?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F=
7%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_mediu=
m=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ), =
an Australian brand that=E2=80=99s been trying to crack the U.S.
market for years, and has partnered with Nordstrom in what feels like their=
 latest attempt to gain traction. But the Cotton On homepage and the Nordst=
rom edit feel very Gap-adjacent, which demonstrates the challenge: American=
 consumers already have a crowded field of low-priced basics to choose from=
=2E=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Alas, without distinctive branding that resonates with U.S. shoppers, it=E2=
=80=99s hard to see Cotton On as
more than another markdown waiting to happen. Nordstrom may be hoping that =
a fresh name will drive interest in their basics business or appeal to the =
Gen Z shopper, but history suggests it won=E2=80=99t. Absent a long-term di=
fferentiation and branding strategy, international basics brands often end =
up as a liquidation at the end of the season, and don=E2=80=99t win the flo=
or space or open-to-buy for the next season.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Still Here, an
indie denim brand, also recently launched a classic unisex sweatshirt ( htt=
ps://go.shopmy.us/p-12891202?utm_campaign=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2=
F7%2F25%29&utm_content=3DLine+Sheet+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%282%2F7%2F25%29&utm_medi=
um=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6c60617da42abd12a ) =
in eight colors. It=E2=80=99s giving American Apparel without the baggage. =
And while sweatshirts for this denim brand may not be a growth category, it=
 is a nice additional purchase to add in the cart.

Everything Else I=E2=80=99m Seeing Out
There=E2=80=A6
--------------------------------

