ything is quiet there.) But in no way does this suggest a bigger brand over=
haul is imminent=E2=80=94some early spring cleaning for social media, perha=
ps, but they didn=E2=80=99t update the website with the new spring delivery=
, and there=E2=80=99s no splashy campaign. After all, this is par for the c=
ourse for the brand: Think about how many times they=E2=80=99ve tweaked the=
 clothing tag in the years since launch. The Row=E2=80=99s whole thing is t=
he pursuit of perfection, even
when what they=E2=80=99re working with is already perfect.

